# LeakSanitizer suppressions for the JaffarPlus test suite.
#
# libnuma's numa_node_of_cpu() (called per worker thread in initializeNUMA) caches a cpumask in
# library-internal thread state that it never frees. This is a 3rd-party allocation, not a JaffarPlus
# leak, and there is no libnuma API to release it -- so suppress it rather than letting it flake the
# multi-threaded asan tests (the count varies with thread scheduling).
leak:numa_node_of_cpu
leak:initializeNUMA
leak:libnuma
